headline: Want $1,000 Per Year in Reliable Dividend Income? Invest $17,300 in These 2 High-Yield Dividend Stocks
summary: Real estate investment trusts, or REITs, are a terrific way for everyday investors to collect rent without owning any buildings themselves.  REITs trade like stocks, but these specialized entities can legally avoid income taxes by distributing at least 90% of their profit to shareholders as dividends.  Realty Income (NYSE: O) and W.P. Carey (NYSE: WPC) are well-established REITs that offer an average yield of 5.8% at recent prices.
